Functional plotting

Functional plotting of input varables across a categorical target.

because Rattle was not fun to use

print(load("data_imp_GMM.RData")) # load and print contents

Mosaic_plotter <- function(dat, x, target) { 
  # x: char string of factor input name in dat
  # target: char string of factor target name in dat
  mosaicplot(as.formula(paste0("~ ", x, " + ", target)), data = dat,
             main=paste0("Mosaic of ", x, " by ", target),
             color=colorspace::rainbow_hcl(3)[-1], cex=0.7, xlab=x, ylab=target)
}

cluster_plotter <- function(dat, x, target) {
  # x: char string of num input name in dat
  # target: char string of factor cluster name in dat
  dat %>%
    dplyr::select(.data[[x]], .data[[target]]) %>%
    ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(x=.data[[x]])) +
    ggplot2::geom_density(lty=3) +
    ggplot2::geom_density(ggplot2::aes(fill=.data[[target]],
                                       colour=.data[[target]]),
                          alpha=0.55,
                          show.legend = F) +
    ggplot2::scale_fill_brewer(palette ="Set1") +
    ggplot2::labs(title = paste0("Distribution of ", x,
                                 "\nby ", target,"."),
                  x=x, y="Density",fill=target)
}

Single plots

Plotting a categorical input and binary target.

# single plots
Mosaic_plotter(data.imp.GMM, "cluster", "Book_12Mo")

Plotting a numerical input and binary target.

# single plots
cluster_plotter(data.imp.GMM, "Grp_Size", "cluster")

Here cluster is a varable defined by fitting Gaussian Mixture Model classification clusters with a set of survey response variables.

All plots

categorical inputs

Plotting all categorical inputs vs the binary target.

# all cat inputs
II <- set_names(names(data.imp.GMM[indx$cat]))

iwalk(II, ~{
  Mosaic_plotter(data.imp.GMM, .x, "Book_12Mo")
})

numerical inputs

Plotting all numerical inputs vs the binary target.

# all num inputs
II <- set_names(names(data.imp.GMM[indx$num]))

iwalk(II, ~{
  print(cluster_plotter(data.imp.GMM, .x, "cluster"))
})
